ğŸ§  Project Description

This project simulates a simple billing calculator. The user interacts with a menu to:

Add item costs to the bill

Subtract discounts

Multiply price by quantity

Divide amounts

View the total bill amount

Exit the program

The bill amount is updated after each operation based on the userâ€™s choice.

ğŸ§® Algorithm

Initialize the total bill amount

Display the billing menu

Read the userâ€™s choice

Perform the selected operation

Update and display the bill amount

Repeat the process until the user exits

ğŸ’» Sample Python Code
price1 = float(input("Enter price of item 1: "))
qty1 = int(input("Enter quantity of item 1: "))

price2 = float(input("Enter price of item 2: "))
qty2 = int(input("Enter quantity of item 2: "))

amount1 = price1 * qty1
amount2 = price2 * qty2

total = amount1 + amount2
print("Total Bill Amount =", total)

